TITLE: Continuous Message Polling in Go
DESCRIPTION: Discusses continuous message retrieval patterns using `Messages()` and `Consume()`. The snippet exemplifies push-like behavior, subject filtering, and error handling, enhancing efficient message fetching and processing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/inngest/blob/main/vendor/github.com/nats-io/nats.go/jetstream/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
cons, _ := js.CreateOrUpdateConsumer("ORDERS", jetstream.ConsumerConfig{
    AckPolicy: jetstream.AckExplicitPolicy,
    // receive messages from ORDERS.A subject only
    FilterSubject: "ORDERS.A"
}))

consContext, _ := c.Consume(func(msg jetstream.Msg) {
    fmt.Printf("Received a JetStream message: %s\n", string(msg.Data()))
})
defer consContext.Stop()
```

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
iter, _ := cons.Messages()
for {
    msg, err := iter.Next()
    // Next can return error, e.g. when iterator is closed or no heartbeats were received
    if err != nil {
        //handle error
    }
    fmt.Printf("Received a JetStream message: %s\n", string(msg.Data()))
    msg.Ack()
}
iter.Stop()
