TITLE: Calling Go Function from Lua with GopherLua
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a Go function `Double` that can be called from Lua. It takes an integer argument from Lua, multiplies it by 2, and returns the result to Lua. The `main` function initializes a Lua state, registers the `Double` function as a global Lua function named "double", and then closes the Lua state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/inngest/blob/main/vendor/github.com/yuin/gopher-lua/README.rst#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func Double(L *lua.LState) int {
    lv := L.ToInt(1)             /* get argument */
    L.Push(lua.LNumber(lv * 2)) /* push result */
    return 1                     /* number of results */
}

func main() {
    L := lua.NewState()
    defer L.Close()
    L.SetGlobal("double", L.NewFunction(Double)) /* Original lua_setglobal uses stack... */
}
```

