TITLE: Encoding Stream with S2 Compression in Go
DESCRIPTION: This function demonstrates how to compress data from an input reader to an output writer using S2 compression. It creates a new S2 writer, copies data from the source to the encoder, and ensures proper closing of the encoder.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/inngest/blob/main/vendor/github.com/klauspost/compress/s2/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Go
CODE:
```
func EncodeStream(src io.Reader, dst io.Writer) error {
    enc := s2.NewWriter(dst)
    _, err := io.Copy(enc, src)
    if err != nil {
        enc.Close()
        return err
    }
    // Blocks until compression is done.
    return enc.Close() 
}
```

