TITLE: Processing Stream Elements with a Goroutine Pool in Go
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to process each element of a stream using a static pool of goroutines. The standard library version uses sync.WaitGroup, while the conc version utilizes the pool package for simpler goroutine management.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/inngest/blob/main/vendor/github.com/sourcegraph/conc/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

