TITLE: Implementing Flag Name Normalization in Go using pflag
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to set a custom flag name normalization function to handle different flag name formats consistently.
SOURCE: https://github.com/inngest/inngest/blob/main/vendor/github.com/spf13/pflag/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func wordSepNormalizeFunc(f *pflag.FlagSet, name string) pflag.NormalizedName {
	from := []string{"-", "_"}
	to := "."
	for _, sep := range from {
		name = strings.Replace(name, sep, to, -1)
	}
	return pflag.NormalizedName(name)
}

myFlagSet.SetNormalizeFunc(wordSepNormalizeFunc)
```

